<HEADLINE> Jobless Claims Number at 10-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The number of Americans filing first-time  
applications for unemployment benefits fell last week and, for 
February, the average level of new applications reached a 10-year 
low. 
</P>
<P>
	Jobless claims totaled a seasonally adjusted 286,000 last week,  
down 8,000 from the week before, the Labor Department said today. 
The four-week moving average of claims, which evens out the 
volatile weekly totals, declined to 290,750, from 293,000 for the 
four-week period ending a week earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	That was the lowest average since February 1989 and reflected  
the continued strength of the American economy. The department was 
scheduled Friday to report the unemployment rate for February and, 
in advance, analysts believed it would hold at a 29-year low of 4.3 
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
