<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Abbott To Market Arthritis Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Abbott Laboratories has acquired U.S.  
co-marketing rights to the drug Mobic, one of a new class of 
arthritis pain medications that promise relief with significantly 
fewer side effects. 
</P>
<P>
	Abbott will sell the drug along with its maker, Germany's  
Boehringer Ingelheim. 
</P>
<P>
	Mobic, under review by the Food and Drug Administration, will  
likely be the third major new arthritis pain drug introduced this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Monsanto and Pfizer already are co-marketing the pain drug  
Celebrex, which has had explosive early sales since it became 
available in January. Merck's Vioxx could be on the market this 
spring. 
</P>
<P>
	The new class of drugs treat pain as well as current  
medications, but are less likely to cause severe stomach problems, 
such as bleeding ulcers, that sometimes occur with older arthritis 
drugs. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
