<HEADLINE> N. Korea Scraps Iowa Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- An official North Korean delegation has  
canceled plans to attend a seminar in Iowa on conflict resolution 
and decided instead to remain in New York to continue discussions 
on nuclear issues with U.S. officials, the State Department said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials from the two countries have been meeting since  
Saturday on U.S. concerns about an underground construction site 
that the Clinton administration believes may involve nuclear 
weapons development. 
</P>
<P>
	The North Korean decision not to attend the Iowa seminar did not  
signify that a breakthrough in the talks was near, an official 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States has demanded unconditional access to the site  
but North Korea has refused. 
</P>
