<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Leafs' McCauley Taken to Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Toronto Maple Leafs center Alyn McCauley was  
taken from the ice on a stretcher after being checked hard into the 
boards early in the third period of a game against the New Jersey 
Devils on Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	McCauley was driven heavily into the end boards by Devils  
defenseman Sheldon Souray at the 6:51 mark of the third period. 
McCauley's left shoulder and head appeared to take the brunt of 
Souray's hit against the glass next to New Jersey goalie Martin 
Brodeur. 
</P>
<P>
	McCauley appeared to lose consciousness and lay motionless on  
the ice for several minutes. He was attended to by four emergency 
personnel including Maple Leafs team doctor Leith Douglas who 
directed the crew to fit McCauley with a neck brace. McCauley was 
lifted onto a stretcher and taken along with his fiancee to Toronto 
Western Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Team officials said that he suffered a head injury and that he  
had movement in all of his extremities. He was to spend the night 
in hospital and be re-examined Thursday. While the injury was not 
considered serious, coach Pat Quinn was concerned. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was unconscious for quite a while,'' Quinn said. ``We won't  
know anything until the evaluation is complete.'' 
</P>
<P>
	New Jersey was leading 3-2 at the time, and the Devils went on  
to a 5-2 victory. The game was delayed about 10 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	It been a tough season for McCauley, who was playing in just his  
fourth game after missing 22 with a knee injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
