<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Higher; Gold Also Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was higher against most other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold also rose. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0811, down from $1.0900. The dollar  
was quoted at 123.43 Japanese yen, up from 121.22. At midday in New 
York, the euro was quoted at $1.0800 and the dollar was quoted at 
123.45 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Wednesday:  
1.4728 Swiss francs, up from 1.4577; 1.5242 Canadian dollars, up 
from 1.5237. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6058, down from $1.6170.  
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8091 German marks, up from 1.7943; 
6.0675 French francs, up from 6.0180; 2.0384 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0218; 1,791.02 Italian lire, up from 1,776.39. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $287.70 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$286.80 on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $287.60, up from $286.10.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold was unchanged in Hong Kong at $286.55.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.29 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$5.25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
