<HEADLINE> Silver Charm Draws for Santa Anita </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Silver Charm, the 8-5 favorite in the  
early line, drew the inside post Thursday for the $1 million Santa 
Anita Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver Charm will carry high weight of 124 pounds and will be  
ridden by Gary Stevens in Saturday's 1 1/4-mile race. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver Charm, who was scratched from last year's race with a  
foot injury, has 12 wins in 21 career starts and has earned 
$6,683,006. 
</P>
<P>
	Others entered Thursday were Sidon, who will be ridden by Gary  
Delahoussaye and carrying 114 pounds; Free House, Chris McCarron, 
123; Puerto Madero, Kent Desormeaux, 122; Dr Fong, Alex Solis, 117; 
and Event Of The Year, Corey Nakatani, 119. 
</P>
<P>
	Puerto Madero, second choice at 2-1, figures to be the top  
challenger to the favorite. Puerto Madero, who upset third-place 
finisher Silver Charm in the Donn Handicap at Gulfstream last 
month, has 11 wins in 16 career starts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
