<HEADLINE> U.S. Soccer Makes Roster Changes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Goalkeeper Zach Thornton and midfielder Frankie  
Hejduk were added Thursday to the U.S. roster for U.S. Cup games 
against Guatemala and Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	Thornton will replace Kasey Keller, who will remain with his  
English club, Leicester City. Tony Sanneh has an injured quadriceps 
and was dropped in favor of Hejduk. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. team will begin training Sunday for the U.S. Cup, a  
four-team exhibition tournament that also includes Bolivia. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's unfortunate that we will not have Kasey in camp once  
again,'' U.S. coach Bruce Arena said. ``But this is another good 
opportunity for Zach Thornton, who has already demonstrated that he 
deserves opportunities with the national team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Leicester City club plays Tottenham Hotspur on March 21 at  
Wembley in the English League Cup final. Leicester is trying to 
become just the fourth team in the 39-year history of the League 
Cup to win the title three times. 
</P>
<P>
	Thornton, who played well in shutting out Chile during the first  
half of the United States' 2-1 victory on Feb. 21, will be joined 
on the roster by goalkeeper Tony Meola. 
</P>
<P>
	Hejduk, a German-based midfielder, will not join the U.S. squad  
until early next week. He is scheduled to play Bayer Leverkusen in 
a Bundesliga match on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The American team opens the U.S. Cup against first-time  
participant Guatemala at the Los Angeles Coliseum next Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
