<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jaguars Re-Sign Cornerback Beasley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Restricted free agent Aaron Beasley,  
who started at cornerback the last two seasons for Jacksonville, 
was one of six players signed Thursday by the Jaguars. 
</P>
<P>
	The others five were reserves; running back Chris Howard,  
linebackers Eddie Mason and Erik Storz and defensive ends Jabbar 
Threats and Lamanzer Williams. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deals were not disclosed, although last month the  
Jaguars tendered the minimum offer of one year and $429,000 to 
Beasley, a three-year veteran who will become an unrestricted free 
agent after next season. He has started 29 of the 34 games he has 
played, and has five career interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
	Threats, an undrafted rookie out of Michigan State in 1997,  
spent the last 12 games of last season on injured reserve with a 
knee injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams saw limited action last season after being drafted in  
the sixth round. 
</P>
<P>
	Howard was signed from the Denver Broncos' practice squad last  
September after James Stewart went down with a knee injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Both Mason and Storz came to the Jaguars in the middle of last  
season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
