<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cole Named New RNC Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Tom Cole, Oklahoma's secretary of state and a  
political consultant, was named chief of staff for the Republican 
National Committee today. 
</P>
<P>
	``Tom brings a wealth of political and administrative experience  
based on his years as a party elected official,'' said RNC chairman 
Jim Nicholson. 
</P>
<P>
	``My loss is definitely the RNC's gain,'' said Oklahoma Gov.  
Frank Keating, who appointed Cole secretary of state in January 
1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Nicholson has been under pressure to strengthen the party's  
political operation after weaker-than-expected results in 
November's midterm elections. Cole is president of a nationally 
recognized public relations, strategic planning and polling firm. 
</P>
<P>
	He was executive director of the GOP House campaign committee  
from 1991 to 1993, an Oklahoma state senator from 1988 to 1991 and 
state party chairman from 1985 to 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
