<HEADLINE> Hawks Reactivate Steve Smith </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- The Atlanta Hawks, struggling to find some  
offense, got their best scorer back Thursday when they reactivated 
guard Steve Smith from the injured list. 
</P>
<P>
	He was expected to play in Thursday night against Toronto.  
</P>
<P>
	Smith, averaging 21.4 points in the Hawks' first nine games,  
sprained his knee Feb. 20. 
</P>
<P>
	In Atlanta's first nine games, the Hawks went 6-3 and averaged  
87.3 points. Since Smith went down, they went 2-4 and averaged 82.2 
points. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room for Smith, the Hawks released Jeff Sheppard, who  
averaged 1.5 points in six games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
