<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 22; Nasdaq Jumps 19 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened higher. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is up 22 points in today's early going. 
Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 7-5 lead over 
decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 19 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up four points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street may be thinking of a little recovery today.  
</P>
<P>
	High-technology stocks appear to have enough strength left over  
from yesterday's gains to give the broader market a small push 
upward today. 
</P>
<P>
	But analysts say any gains may be short-lived.  
</P>
<P>
	There's a key piece of economic information on the way tomorrow  
-- the February unemployment report. 
</P>
<P>
	And with the market already fearful of inflation and higher  
interest rates, any sign of excess strength in tomorrow's numbers 
could be a problem for equities. 
</P>
