<HEADLINE> Falcons-Kanell Deal Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SUWANEE, Ga. (AP) -- The Atlanta Falcons moved close to reaching  
contract terms with Danny Kanell on Thursday, a move that would 
provide backup for quarterback Chris Chandler and reunite Kanell 
with coach Dan Reeves. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've reached an agreement in principle on most things,''  
general manager Harold Richardson said. ``There are still some 
things to be worked out.'' He said a deal could be completed on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Kanell played for Reeves with the New York Giants, where he was  
the starter for most of last season before being benched in 
November after a 3-7 start. He completed 160 passes in 299 attempts 
for 1,603 yards, 11 touchdowns and 10 interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
	Kanell, who was replaced by Kent Graham, was released by the  
Giants last month after they signed Kerry Collins. 
</P>
<P>
	A 1996 fourth-round draft pick out of Florida State, Kanell also  
was sought by the Miami Dolphins, where his father served as team 
physician. 
</P>
<P>
	Kanell started 20 games in three seasons in New York. In 1997,  
he completed 156 of 294 passes for 1,740 yards, 11 TDs and nine 
interceptions after taking over for Dave Brown in midseason and 
helping the Giants win the NFC East. 
</P>
<P>
	Reeves was fired by the Giants after the 1996 season and is in  
his third season in Atlanta. He guided the Falcons to the NFC title 
last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
