<HEADLINE> Lynn Redgrave Files for Divorce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Lynn Redgrave, supporting actress Oscar  
nominee for ``Gods and Monsters,'' has filed for divorce from her 
husband of nearly 32 years. 
</P>
<P>
	In a one-page document filed under her married name, Lynn Clark,  
she cited irreconcilable differences as the reason for the split 
with husband John Clark, who is also her manager. 
</P>
<P>
	The couple, who have a 17-year-old daughter living at home, wed  
April 2, 1967. 
</P>
<P>
	No other details were available. Miss Redgrave and Clark  
couldn't be reached through attorney Emily Shappell Edelman, who 
filed the divorce petition Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Redgrave, the younger sister of actress Vanessa Redgrave,  
has appeared in ``Georgy Girl,'' ``Midnight'' and ``Everything You 
Always Wanted to Know About Sex.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
