<HEADLINE> Browns Sign Running Back Kirby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- The Cleveland Browns signed running back Terry  
Kirby on Thursday, making him the sixth former San Francisco 49er 
to join the expansion club. 
</P>
<P>
	Kirby, 29, played three seasons with Miami and three with San  
Francisco. He was a third-round pick by the Dolphins in 1993 out of 
Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
	Kirby has 2,272 career yards rushing on 594 carries, and has  
caught 246 passes for 2,498 yards. He has caught 50 or more passes 
in three of his six NFL seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	``Terry brings us tremendous versatility at the running back  
position,'' said Dwight Clark, vice president of football 
operations for the Browns. Clark previously held the same position 
with San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
	Kirby ``not only is a proven running back, but one of the most  
successful receiving backs,'' Clark said. 
</P>
<P>
	Kirby is the brother of former Indians outfielder Wayne Kirby.  
</P>
