<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 13:47:00 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Secret Service Director Sworn In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Brian L. Stafford, former head of President  
Clinton's security detail, was sworn in Thursday as the 20th 
director of the Secret Service. 
</P>
<P>
	Stafford, 51, replaces Lou Merletti, who retired two months ago  
to run the security operation for the Cleveland Browns football 
team. Merletti fought to keep Secret Service agents from testifying 
in the Monica Lewinsky investigation, but the courts ruled against 
him. 
</P>
<P>
	Stafford, a 28-year veteran of the Secret Service, is a native  
of Sharpsville, Pa. He served in the Army prior to joining the 
agency, serving a tour of duty in Vietnam from 1969 to 1971. He was 
head of Clinton's security detail for about a year, but did not 
testify in the inquiry. 
</P>
<P>
	``Brian has distinguished himself and the Secret Service thorugh  
his professionalism, integrity and commitment to duty,'' said 
Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin, who oversees the agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
